# bao-boss — Cursor Rules

## Project

Bun-native PostgreSQL job queue library with SKIP LOCKED concurrency, retries, cron scheduling, pub/sub, dead letter queues, and an HTMX dashboard.

## Stack

- Runtime: Bun (not Node.js)
- HTTP: Elysia (type-safe routes)
- ORM: Prisma 7 + PrismaPg adapter (schema + migrations) + raw SQL for SKIP LOCKED
- Dashboard: htmx (server-rendered HTML, no JS frameworks)
- Validation: TypeBox (`@sinclair/typebox`)
- Language: TypeScript strict mode
- Database: PostgreSQL 15+ with `baoboss` schema

## Conventions

- Use Bun APIs: `bun test`, `bun run`, `bunx prisma`
- ESNext modules with `.js` import extensions
- TypeScript strict with `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`
- All DB tables in `baoboss` PostgreSQL schema
- Prisma 7 for CRUD (import from `src/generated/prisma/`), raw SQL only for `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED`
- Validate inputs with TypeBox schemas (`Type` + `Value.Decode`) in Manager.ts
- Dashboard: inline HTML strings with htmx attributes
- Emit errors via `boss.emit('error', err)` — never swallow
- Tests in `packages/bao-boss/test/` using `bun test`

## Key Files

- `packages/bao-boss/src/BaoBoss.ts` — Main class, lifecycle
- `packages/bao-boss/src/Manager.ts` — Job/queue CRUD, SKIP LOCKED
- `packages/bao-boss/src/Worker.ts` — Polling worker
- `packages/bao-boss/src/Scheduler.ts` — Cron schedules
- `packages/bao-boss/src/Maintenance.ts` — Background supervisor
- `packages/bao-boss/src/Dashboard.ts` — Elysia htmx plugin
- `packages/bao-boss/src/types.ts` — TypeScript types
- `packages/bao-boss/prisma/schema.prisma` — DB schema
